   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>VI.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>THERE BEING A GREAT DAY,</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>A TIME OF DISTRESS, FOR ISRAEL</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Jeremiah 30:5-8 reveals that there will be a great day, a time of distress, for Israel.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>A. The Time of the Great Tribulation</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>for Three and a Half Years</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Verse 7a says, "Alas!</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>For that day is great, / And there is none like it; / And it is a time of distress for Jacob."</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>This great day, this time of distress, is the time of the great tribulation for three and a half years Matt 24:21; Dan 12:7b; Rev 13:5, 7a .</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Jeremiah 30 refers to the great tribulation during the last three and a half years of this age.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>B. Israel Being Saved out of It</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Jeremiah 30:7b tells us that Israel will be saved out of this great tribulation Dan 12:1 .</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>C. Jehovah Breaking Israel's Yoke</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>from upon Her Neck</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>and Tearing Off Her Bonds</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>In Jeremiah 30:8 Jehovah promised that, in that day, He will break the yoke from upon Israel's neck and tear off her bonds.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>The strangers will no longer make her serve them.</S>
   </TEXT>
